%e A334485 The Gosper curve starts (on a hexagonal lattice) as follows:
%e A334485      .   .   .   .   .   +---+---+   .   .   .   .
%e A334485                           \       \
%e A334485        .   .   +---+---+   +---+   +   .   .   .   .
%e A334485                 \       \     /   /
%e A334485      .   .   .   +---+   +---+   +   +---+   .   .
%e A334485                     /             \   \   \
%e A334485        .   .   +---+   +---+---+   +   +   +   .   .
%e A334485               /         \       \   \ /    49
%e A334485      .   .   +   +---+   +---+   +   +   .   .   .
%e A334485               \   \   \     /   /
%e A334485        .   .   +   +   +---+   +   +---+   .   .   .
%e A334485                 \ /             \ /   /10
%e A334485      .   .   .   +   +---+---+   +   +   .   .   .
%e A334485                  25   \       \     /9
%e A334485        .   .   .   .   +---+   +---+   .   .   .   .
%e A334485                           /    7   8
%e A334485      .   .   .   .   +---+   .   .   .   .   .   .
%e A334485                      0   1
%e A334485 - hence a(8) = a(9) = a(10) = a(50) = 3.
